Not every photo or edit needs to be released. I’ll edit a photo ten times and still not drop it. Even if I do, I might archive it. The likes don’t mean anything. At the end of the day, week, month… I need to look at my feed and feel that I put out a solid body of work. Producing daily, making videos and putting out mediocre posts for likes might work for engagement…but what does that mean? People are paying monthly for check marks now. People are paying by spending all there time on social and not doing shit in the real world. People are paying with their emotions when their post don’t pan out. You see somebody ballin out on social these days and you know they’re paying the biggest price.
Just because I don’t, doesn’t mean I can’t 😂

People swallow their love before they swallow their pride✍️

I’ve shot ports maybe twice this last year, but I edit multiple times a day. Finding the drive to post, when I see such mediocrity, creeps, and fakes succeed is draining. I’ve spent nearly a lifetime trying to master photography, videography, and editing. The industry has done me so dirty, I could make a reality show. Long Story short, post what you want, when you want. At the end of the day nobody gives a sh!t, when you’re doing good in life and not posting every moment of your sh!t on ig. They’re not calling, messaging…There’s a reason why they are called VANITY METRICS.
